Muguruza's first event of the year was to be the [[2015_Brisbane_International|Brisbane International]] but she was forced to withdraw from the event due to an ankle injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxsports.com.au/tennis/womens-tour/brisbane-international-2015-eighth-seed-garbine-muguruza-withdraws/story-fn2msfn9-1227174811204|title=Brisbane International 2015: Eighth seed Garbine Muguruza withdraws|work=Fox Sports|accessdate=26 April 2015|archive-date=2020-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401022603/https://www.foxsports.com.au/tennis/brisbane-international-2015-eighth-seed-garbine-muguruza-withdraws/news-story/289489d020c717770208586543fd2b30?nk=aa2f61dbc852939c895f77fe7ee87dbb-1585707963|dead-url=no}}</ref> The following week, Muguruza chose not to defend her title at the [[2015_Hobart_International|Hobart International]] and competed at the [[2015_Apia_International_Sydney|Sydney International]] instead, where she reached the quarterfinals, defeating [[Agnieszka_Radwańska|Agnieszka Radwańska]] for the first time in her career en route.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apiainternational.com.au/2015/01/muguruza-upsets-radwanska-in-three|title=Muguruza upsets Radwanska, Kvitova powers through|publisher=apiainterinational.com.au|accessdate=26 April 2015|archive-date=2017-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170228003322/http://www.apiainternational.com.au/2015/01/muguruza-upsets-radwanska-in-three|dead-url=no}}</ref> At the [[2015_Australian_Open|Australian Open]], she progressed to the fourth round for the second consecutive year with wins over [[Marina_Erakovic|Marina Erakovic]], [[Daniela_Hantuchová|Daniela Hantuchová]] and [[Timea_Bacsinszky|Timea Bacsinszky]] before falling to the eventual champion, [[Serena_Williams|Serena Williams]] in three sets.

Muguruza won both of her singles rubbers in the [[2015_Fed_Cup_World_Group_II|2015 Fed Cup World Group II]], defeating [[Irina-Camelia_Begu|Irina-Camelia Begu]] and world No. 3 [[Simona_Halep|Simona Halep]] but Spain lost the tie 3–2 after Muguruza and her compatriot, [[Anabel_Medina_Garrigues|Anabel Medina Garrigues]] lost the deciding doubles rubber. At the [[2015_Dubai_Tennis_Championships|Dubai Tennis Championships]], Muguruza reached her first WTA Premier 5 semi-final in singles, defeating qualifier [[Jarmila_Gajdošová|Jarmila Gajdošová]], twelfth seed [[Jelena_Janković|Jelena Janković]], fifth seed [[Agnieszka_Radwańska|Agnieszka Radwańska]] and thirteenth seed and doubles partner [[Carla_Suárez_Navarro|Carla Suárez Navarro]] before falling to the seventeenth seed and eventual runner-up, [[Karolína_Plíšková|Karolína Plíšková]] in three sets. She also reached the final of the [[2015_Dubai_Tennis_Championships_–_Women's_Doubles|doubles]] with Suárez Navarro. The following week, Muguruza retired from her first round match against Suárez Navarro at the [[2015_Qatar_Total_Open|Qatar Open]] while trailing 6–5 in the first set.

In March, Muguruza lost to Ka. Plíšková in the third round of the [[2015_BNP_Paribas_Open|Indian Wells Masters]] after a second round win over American wildcard [[Irina_Falconi|Irina Falconi]]. Despite this, she rose to a career high singles ranking of world No. 19 after the event. A fortnight later, Muguruza reached the third round of the [[2015_Miami_Open|Miami Open]] after defeating qualifier [[Sesil_Karatantcheva|Sesil Karatantcheva]] but lost to the eleventh seed [[Sara_Errani|Sara Errani]] after winning the first set.

Muguruza reached the second round of the three clay court events that she competed in leading into the [[2015_French_Open|French Open]]. She lost to second seed Simona Halep in [[2015_Porsche_Tennis_Grand_Prix|Stuttgart]], [[Kristina_Mladenovic|Kristina Mladenovic]] in [[2015_Grand_Prix_SAR_La_Princesse_Lalla_Meryem|Marrakech]] and the eventual finalist [[Svetlana_Kuznetsova|Svetlana Kuznetsova]] in [[2015_Mutua_Madrid_Open|Madrid]]. Muguruza and Suárez Navarro also reached the [[2015_Mutua_Madrid_Open_–_Women's_Doubles|doubles]] final of the latter for the second consecutive year but the pair lost in three sets to [[Casey_Dellacqua|Casey Dellacqua]] and [[Yaroslava_Shvedova|Yaroslava Shvedova]]. Despite failing to win back-to-back matches since February, Muguruza reached her second consecutive French Open quarterfinal, defeating [[Angelique_Kerber|Angelique Kerber]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.axs.com/news/kerber-loses-in-third-round-upset-55768|title=Muguruza beats in-form Kerber to reach fourth round|work=AXS|date=29 May 2015|accessdate=7 July 2015|archive-date=2017-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002022303/https://www.axs.com/news/kerber-loses-in-third-round-upset-55768|dead-url=no}}</ref> and [[Flavia_Pennetta|Flavia Pennetta]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.efe.com/efe/english/destacada/muguruza-breezes-into-french-open-quarterfinals/50000261-2628015#|title=Muguruza into another French quarters|work=EFE|date=1 June 2015|accessdate=7 July 2015|archive-date=2017-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001214339/https://www.efe.com/efe/english/destacada/muguruza-breezes-into-french-open-quarterfinals/50000261-2628015|dead-url=no}}</ref> en route, before losing to the eventual runner-up, [[Lucie_Šafářová|Lucie Šafářová]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/news/french-open-women-lucie-safarova-beats-garbine-muguruza-140515786--ten.html|title=Safarova beats Muguruza to make last four|work=Yahoo! Sport|date=2 June 2015|accessdate=7 July 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707052202/https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/news/french-open-women-lucie-safarova-beats-garbine-muguruza-140515786--ten.html|archivedate=2015年7月7日}}</ref>

