Muguruza made a poor start to the [[grass_court|grass court]] season, losing in the first round of the [[2015_Aegon_Classic|Birmingham Classic]] and the third round of the [[2015_Aegon_International|Eastbourne International]] after a first round bye. However, she and Suárez Navarro won their first grass court [[2015_Aegon_International_–_Doubles|doubles]] title in Birmingham, defeating [[Andrea_Hlaváčková|Andrea Hlaváčková]] and [[Lucie_Hradecká|Lucie Hradecká]] in straight sets in the final. At the [[2015_Wimbledon_Championships|Wimbledon Championships]], Muguruza defeated 10th seed Kerber in the third round,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/tennis/article-3149406/Garbine-Muguruza-face-World-No-5-Caroline-Wozniacki-Wimbledon-2015-round-scalp-Angelique-Kerber.html|title=Garbine Muguruza to face world No. 5 Caroline Wozniacki at Wimbledon 2015 after third round scalp of Angelique Kerber|work=Daily Mail|accessdate=7 July 2015|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305082239/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/tennis/article-3149406/Garbine-Muguruza-face-World-No-5-Caroline-Wozniacki-Wimbledon-2015-round-scalp-Angelique-Kerber.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 5th seed [[Caroline_Wozniacki|Caroline Wozniacki]] in the fourth round,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/tennis/wimbledon-2015-caroline-wozniacki-goes-out-to-garbine-muguruza--and-takes-a-swipe-at-officialdom-10370418.html|title=Wimbledon 2015: Caroline Wozniacki goes out to Garbine Muguruza – and takes a swipe at officialdom|publisher=independent.co.uk|accessdate=7 July 2015|archive-date=2015-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925233647/http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/tennis/wimbledon-2015-caroline-wozniacki-goes-out-to-garbine-muguruza--and-takes-a-swipe-at-officialdom-10370418.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 15th seed [[Timea_Bacsinszky|Timea Bacsinszky]] in the quarterfinals and 13th seed [[Agnieszka_Radwańska|Agnieszka Radwańska]] in the semi-finals to advance to her maiden Grand Slam final. She played against world No. 1 [[Serena_Williams|Serena Williams]] for the title, but lost in straight sets.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/jul/11/serena-williams-beats-garbine-muguruza-wimbledon-grand-slam|title= Serena Williams beats battling Garbiñe Muguruza to win Wimbledon|date= 11 July 2015|work= The Guardian|accessdate= 14 July 2015|archive-date= 2017-07-12|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170712183549/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/jul/11/serena-williams-beats-garbine-muguruza-wimbledon-grand-slam|dead-url= no}}</ref> After the tournament, Muguruza entered the Top 10 for the first time, moving up to world No. 9 in the [[WTA_Rankings|WTA Rankings]].

During the [[2015_US_Open_Series|US Open series]], Muguruza did not enjoy much success, dropping her opening matches in [[2015_Rogers_Cup|Toronto]] and [[2015_Western_&_Southern_Open|Cincinnati]] to qualifiers [[Lesia_Tsurenko|Lesia Tsurenko]] and [[Yaroslava_Shvedova|Yaroslava Shvedova]] respectively. At the [[2015_US_Open_(tennis)|US Open]], she recorded her first win at the tournament by defeating German [[Carina_Witthöft|Carina Witthöft]] in the first round. However, she fell short to [[Johanna_Konta|Johanna Konta]] in the following round in three sets, the match was a total time of 3 hours and 23 minutes, the longest women's singles match in that tournament's history since the introduction of tiebreaker in 1970.

Muguruza kicked off the Asian swing at the [[2015_Toray_Pan_Pacific_Open|Pan Pacific Open]] where she successfully advanced to the last eight after defeating [[Barbora_Strýcová|Barbora Strýcová]] before losing to eventual finalist [[Belinda_Bencic|Belinda Bencic]] in straight sets. At the [[2015_Wuhan_Open|Wuhan Open]], Muguruza successfully cruised into her second straight quarterfinal at the event after dispatching [[Sloane_Stephens|Sloane Stephens]] and [[Ana_Ivanovic|Ana Ivanovic]]. She then went on to defeat the likes of [[Anna_Karolina_Schmiedlova|Anna Karolina Schmiedlova]] and Kerber to reach the final where she faced [[Venus_Williams|Venus Williams]] but was forced to retire in the second set with an ankle injury. Muguruza was able to crack the Top 5 for the first time in her career after the tournament's conclusion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wtatennis.com/news/article/5048612/title/garbine-muguruza-the-new-world-no5|title=GARBIÑE MUGURUZA: The New world No. 5=WTATennis.com|date=5 October 2015|accessdate=5 October 2015|archive-date=2015-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110011242/http://www.wtatennis.com/news/article/5048612/title/garbine-muguruza-the-new-world-no5|dead-url=no}}</ref> At the [[2015_China_Open_(tennis)|China Open]], Muguruza breezed by [[Irina_Falconi|Irina Falconi]] before going the distance against [[Mirjana_Lučić-Baroni|Mirjana Lučić-Baroni]] to advance to the quarterfinals. With the win, Muguruza qualified for the [[2015_WTA_Finals|WTA Finals]] for the first time. She will be the first Spaniard to compete at the year-end championships since [[Arantxa_Sánchez_Vicario|Arantxa Sánchez Vicario]] in 2001. She then beat [[Bethanie_Mattek-Sands|Bethanie Mattek-Sands]] and Radwańska to advance to her maiden Premier Mandatory final. With her semifinal win over Radwańska, Muguruza cracked the Top 4 rankings where she reached a career high of world No. 4. She went on to defeat Bacsinszky in straight sets to claim her first Premier Mandatory title and her biggest title of her career.

Muguruza then traveled to Singapore for the [[2015_WTA_Finals|WTA Finals]], where she went undefeated in the round robin play; beating [[Petra_Kvitová|Petra Kvitová]], [[Angelique_Kerber|Angelique Kerber]], and [[Lucie_Šafářová|Lucie Šafářová]]. She then lost to eventual champion [[Agnieszka_Radwańska|Agnieszka Radwańska]] in the semifinals. Muguruza also competed in doubles in Singapore, where she and her compatriot [[Carla_Suárez_Navarro|Carla Suárez Navarro]] reached the final. However, they lost to the number one seeds [[Martina_Hingis|Martina Hingis]] and [[Sania_Mirza|Sania Mirza]].
